   "id": "4a5a77cf-ba49-4a35-9963-a86824dc8b2f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Automatic Feature Selection Using Lasso Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how Lasso (Least Absolute Shrinkage and Selection Operator) regression performs **automatic feature selection** by shrinking less important feature coefficients to exactly zero. This is a powerful technique for reducing model complexity and improving interpretability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "concept-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## The Lasso Regression Cost Function\n",
    "\n",
    "Lasso minimizes the following objective function:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{Cost} = \\frac{1}{2N_{training}} \\sum_{i=1}^{N_{training}} (Y_{real}^{(i)} - Y_{predict}^{(i)})^2 + \\alpha \\sum_{j=1}^{N}|a_j|$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Where:**\n",
    "- **First term**: Mean squared error (prediction loss) - measures how well the model fits the data\n",
    "- **Second term**: L1 regularization penalty (sum of absolute values of coefficients)\n",
    "- **α (alpha)**: Regularization strength parameter that controls the trade-off between fitting the data and keeping coefficients small\n",
    "- **N**: Total number of features\n",
    "- **a_j**: The coefficient for feature j\n",
    "\n",
    "## How Lasso Performs Feature Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Coefficient Shrinkage**: The L1 penalty encourages the algorithm to minimize coefficients as much as possible\n",
    "2. **Sparsity**: Unlike Ridge regression (L2), Lasso can shrink coefficients **exactly to zero** (not just close to zero)\n",
    "3. **Automatic Selection**: Features with zero coefficients are effectively removed from the model\n",
    "4. **Collinearity Handling**: If two features are collinear (highly correlated), Lasso will keep only one and set the other's coefficient to zero, automatically addressing multicollinearity\n",
    "\n",
    "## Key Advantages\n",
    "- ✅ **Automatic feature selection** without manual intervention\n",
    "- ✅ **Reduced model complexity** (fewer features → easier interpretation)\n",
    "- ✅ **Better generalization** (reduced overfitting)\n",
    "- ✅ **Computational efficiency** (fewer features to compute with)\n",
    "- ✅ **Handles multicollinearity** by selecting one feature from correlated sets\n",
    "\n",
    "## Important Note\n",
    "**Lasso works best on scaled/normalized data** because the L1 penalty treats all features equally. Without scaling, features with larger values would have an unfair advantage in the regularization process."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "import-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Import Required Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "5af8fbdf-1c48-411d-98e0-321df594acaa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_diabetes\n",
    "\n",
    "# Suppress warnings for cleaner output (optional)\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "data-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Load and Prepare the Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll use the **Diabetes dataset** from scikit-learn:\n",
    "- **442 samples** with 10 features each\n",
    "- Features represent various physiological measurements\n",
    "- Target: quantitative measure of disease progression\n",
    "- Feature names: age, sex, bmi, bp, s1, s2, s3, s4, s5, s6"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "7db2f3ac-4bb3-418f-8080-51b12520ce66",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load dataset\n",
    "X, y = load_diabetes(return_X_y=True)\n",
    "features = load_diabetes()['feature_names']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape: {X.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Number of features: {len(features)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Features: {list(features)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "split-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Split Data and Create Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "We create a pipeline that:\n",
    "1. **StandardScaler**: Normalizes features to have mean=0 and std=1 (required for Lasso to work properly)\n",
    "2. **Lasso**: Applies Lasso regression for feature selection\n",
    "\n",
    "Pipelines are useful because they ensure the same preprocessing is applied consistently to both training and test data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "344f8054-6c3f-4905-b3ad-c4d55fa7349d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Split data into training (67%) and testing (33%) sets\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, \n",
    "    test_size=0.33, \n",
    "    random_state=42  # For reproducibility\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Training set size: {X_train.shape[0]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Test set size: {X_test.shape[0]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a pipeline with scaling and Lasso\n",
    "pipeline = Pipeline([\n",
    "    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),  # Normalize features to mean=0, std=1\n",
    "    ('model', Lasso())              # Lasso regression model\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "gridsearch-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Hyperparameter Tuning with GridSearchCV\n",
    "\n",
    "### Understanding `model__alpha` - The Key Parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "The **alpha (α)** parameter is the **regularization strength** that controls the amount of feature selection:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Alpha Value | Effect | Use Case |\n",
    "|-------------|--------|----------|\n",
    "| **α = 0** | No regularization (equivalent to standard Linear Regression) | Fit all features without any penalty |\n",
    "| **0 < α < 1** | Mild regularization | Slight coefficient shrinkage, most features retained |\n",
    "| **α ≈ 1-3** | Strong regularization | Many coefficients set to zero (aggressive feature selection) |\n",
    "| **α >> 3** | Very strong regularization | Most/all coefficients become zero (very few or no features selected) |\n",
    "\n",
    "### How to Choose Alpha?\n",
    "We use **GridSearchCV with cross-validation** to automatically find the optimal alpha:\n",
    "- Test multiple alpha values (0.1 to 3.0 in steps of 0.1)\n",
    "- Use 5-fold cross-validation to evaluate each alpha\n",
    "- Select the alpha with the lowest mean squared error\n",
    "- This provides a data-driven approach rather than manual tuning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "89d9e146-0b98-4158-af12-b125b390bccc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define hyperparameter grid for alpha\n",
    "param_grid = {\n",
    "    'model__alpha': np.arange(0.1, 3, 0.1)  # Test 29 different alpha values\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create GridSearchCV object\n",
    "search = GridSearchCV(\n",
    "    pipeline,\n",
    "    param_grid,\n",
    "    cv=5,                              # 5-fold cross-validation\n",
    "    scoring='neg_mean_squared_error',  # Minimize MSE (negative because sklearn uses convention: higher is better)\n",
    "    verbose=1                          # Print progress information\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"GridSearchCV configured:\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Testing 29 different alpha values\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Using 5-fold cross-validation\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Objective: Minimize mean squared error\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fit-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Train the Model\n",
    "\n",
    "This step performs cross-validation over all alpha values:\n",
    "1. For each alpha value\n",
    "2. Train the model 5 times (one for each fold)\n",
    "3. Evaluate performance on held-out fold\n",
    "4. Calculate average performance across all folds\n",
    "5. Select alpha with best average performance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d86f48fc-fcc5-4672-878f-03357ddb7268",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fit the model using GridSearchCV\n",
    "search.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "print(\"Model training completed!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "results-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6: Analyze Results\n",
    "\n",
    "### Best Hyperparameters Found"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "37b519a0-03a8-4c8c-a9f5-165a76325cd7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'model__alpha': 1.2000000000000002}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 16,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Display the best alpha found by GridSearchCV\n",
    "print(\"Best Hyperparameters:\")\n",
    "print(search.best_params_)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nOptimal Alpha Value: {search.best_params_['model__alpha']:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Best Cross-Validation Score (neg_MSE): {search.best_score_:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nInterpretation: Alpha = 1.2 provides the best balance\")\n",
    "print(\"between prediction accuracy and feature selection.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "coef-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Extracted Model Coefficients\n",
    "\n",
    "Each coefficient represents the weight/importance of a feature in the model. Zero coefficients mean the feature was eliminated by Lasso."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "43d8ab04-c4b6-4136-92e7-9846766e7eeb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extract coefficients from the best model\n",
    "coef = search.best_estimator_[1].coef_  # [1] accesses the 'model' step from the pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Model Coefficients (Feature Weights):\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*40)\n",
    "for feature, coefficient in zip(features, coef):\n",
    "    status = \"[SELECTED]\" if coefficient != 0 else \"[ELIMINATED]\"\n",
    "    print(f\"{feature:5s}: {coefficient:8.4f}  {status}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "selected-features-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Features Selected by Lasso (Non-Zero Coefficients)\n",
    "\n",
    "These are the features that Lasso determined to be important for predicting disease progression."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "92d84407-f048-400e-870b-724c867dc88c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array(['age', 'sex', 'bmi', 'bp', 's1', 's3', 's5'], dtype='<U3')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 14,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Identify features with non-zero coefficients (selected features)\n",
    "selected_features = np.array(features)[coef != 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Selected Features ({len(selected_features)} out of {len(features)}):\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*40)\n",
    "print(selected_features)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFeature Selection Rate: {len(selected_features)/len(features)*100:.1f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nThese {len(selected_features)} features are sufficient for predictions.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "discarded-features-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Features Eliminated by Lasso (Zero Coefficients)\n",
    "\n",
    "These features were determined to be less important or redundant for predicting disease progression. Lasso automatically set their coefficients to exactly zero, removing them from the model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "5026e4c8-8be9-4383-9d7b-a800581dfa46",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array(['s2', 's4', 's6'], dtype='<U3')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 15,
     "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
    "source": [
    "# Identify features with zero coefficients (eliminated features)\n",
    "eliminated_features = np.array(features)[coef == 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Eliminated Features ({len(eliminated_features)} out of {len(features)}):\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*40)\n",
    "print(eliminated_features)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFeature Elimination Rate: {len(eliminated_features)/len(features)*100:.1f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nReason for elimination:\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Low predictive power (don't help reduce MSE)\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Collinear with other features (redundant information)\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Adding them increases the L1 penalty without improving fit\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "summary-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary & Key Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "### Results:\n",
    "1. **Optimal Alpha**: The grid search determined that **α = 1.2** provides the best balance between model fit and feature selection\n",
    "2. **Features Selected**: **7 out of 10** features were retained in the model (70%)\n",
    "3. **Features Eliminated**: **3 features** (s2, s4, s6) were automatically excluded due to their low predictive value or collinearity\n",
    "4. **Model Simplification**: We reduced model complexity by 30% while maintaining good predictive performance\n",
    "\n",
    "### Advantages Demonstrated:\n",
    "- ✅ **Automatic feature selection** - No need to manually choose which features to keep\n",
    "- ✅ **Reduced complexity** - Simpler models are easier to interpret and understand\n",
    "- ✅ **Better generalization** - Smaller model is less prone to overfitting\n",
    "- ✅ **Computational efficiency** - Fewer features mean faster predictions\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to Use Lasso:\n",
    "- **High-dimensional datasets** with many features\n",
    "- **Need for interpretability** - Understand which features matter\n",
    "- **Suspected multicollinearity** - Correlated features in the data\n",
    "- **Want automatic feature selection** - Instead of manual feature engineering\n",
    "- **Prevent overfitting** - When model complexity needs to be controlled\n",
    "\n",
    "### Comparison with Similar Methods:\n",
    "- **Ridge Regression (L2)**: Shrinks coefficients but doesn't set them to zero\n",
    "- **Elastic Net**: Combines L1 and L2 penalties for balanced feature selection\n",
    "- **Manual Feature Selection**: Time-consuming and potentially biased"
   ]
  }
 ],
